race.comment: SAINT MARGARET (12) will find this a little easier than her third on debut a month ago, beaten 2 lengths at the end of 1106m at Saratoga (Turf). Has plenty of upside so she should be in the finish again. RAYNHAM HALL (13) missed the frame on debut then progressed nicely at her second outing when prominent at the bend, finishing 1.5 lengths from the winner in second at the end of 1106m at Saratoga. Has her share of talent. Hard to beat in this suitable race. MARIA CALLAS (1) faced the starter for the first time and was well supported but could only manage ninth last start at Saratoga (Turf) over 1710m, beaten 10 lengths. Improver who can feature in the finish. ISLAND CHARM (8) ran a fair race on debut last time out, beaten 5 lengths into fifth over 1106m at Saratoga (Turf) on September 1. Can sneak into the finish. Something for the Multiples: SASSY SATS (11)
